WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

2
00:01:59.705 --> 00:02:02.291
- Good morrow. Lady Rhea.
- Cousin.

3
00:02:02.374 --> 00:02:04.334
What's today's quarry? Rabbit?

4
00:02:04.835 --> 00:02:07.963
- Deer.
- Oh. fine challenge.

5
00:02:08.046 --> 00:02:09.506
Care for some company?

6
00:02:09.589 --> 00:02:10.882
I'd rather ride alone.

7
00:02:13.302 --> 00:02:14.553
Good fortune to you.

8
00:03:01.725 --> 00:03:02.809
Husband.

9
00:03:08.357 --> 00:03:09.608
What brings you to the Vale?

10
00:03:14.196 --> 00:03:18.158
Or have you at last come
to consummate our marriage?

11
00:03:19.701 --> 00:03:22.245
The Vale's sheep might be willing.

12
00:03:22.329 --> 00:03:23.789
even if I'm not.

13
00:03:24.664 --> 00:03:27.542
Our sheep are prettier. after all.

14
00:03:29.044 --> 00:03:32.756
Or perhaps your brother has at last
had his fill of your company.

15
00:03:33.799 --> 00:03:36.760
Cast you aside
in favor of a little girl.

16
00:03:42.933 --> 00:03:44.518
What will you do now?

17
00:03:45.477 --> 00:03:48.605
Will you strike the child down?

18
00:03:48.688 --> 00:03:49.981
Or?

19
00:04:39.239 --> 00:04:41.116
I knew you couldn't finish.

20
00:04:43.034 --> 00:04:44.244
Craven!

21
00:05:24.159 --> 00:05:25.577
Thank you.

22
00:06:07.202 --> 00:06:08.370
A moment.

23
00:06:15.794 --> 00:06:17.170
I do not wish to see you go.

24
00:06:20.215 --> 00:06:22.133
Such is the King's decision.

25
00:06:22.217 --> 00:06:23.969
A decision I most bitterly regret.

26
00:06:27.013 --> 00:06:29.015
And yet. you made it possible.

27
00:06:31.226 --> 00:06:32.727
You chose Rhaenyra.

28
00:06:34.187 --> 00:06:35.730
She swore her innocence.

29
00:06:35.814 --> 00:06:37.357
and I believed her.

30
00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:40.443
You wanted to believe her.
as did her father.

31
00:06:40.527 --> 00:06:41.945
Your informant was wrong.

32
00:06:42.028 --> 00:06:44.864
An honest mistake. perhaps.
but I did not foresee this!

33
00:06:44.948 --> 00:06:46.533
You should have.

34
00:06:46.616 --> 00:06:49.786
If you had not been so relentless
in advancing Aegon as heir!

35
00:07:00.463 --> 00:07:01.756
Listen to me. daughter.

36
00:07:03.133 --> 00:07:05.176
The King will die.

37
00:07:05.260 --> 00:07:08.555
It may be months or years.
but he'll not live to be an old man.

38
00:07:08.638 --> 00:07:10.599
And if Rhaenyra succeeds him.

39
00:07:10.682 --> 00:07:14.019
war will follow. do you understand?

40
00:07:14.102 --> 00:07:15.895
The realm will not accept her.

41
00:07:15.979 --> 00:07:17.480
And to secure her claim.

42
00:07:17.564 --> 00:07:20.233
she'll have to put
your children to the sword.

43
00:07:20.317 --> 00:07:21.610
She'll have no choice.

44
00:07:24.613 --> 00:07:26.323
You know it.

45
00:07:26.406 --> 00:07:30.076
You're no fool.
and yet you choose not to see it.

46
00:07:32.329 --> 00:07:34.456
The time is coming. Alicent.

47
00:07:35.915 --> 00:07:38.418
Either you prepare Aegon to rule.

48
00:07:38.501 --> 00:07:42.714
or you cleave to Rhaenyra
and pray for her mercy.

49
00:09:15.974 --> 00:09:19.561
Where is Lord Corlys?
He should be here to receive the King.

50
00:09:28.486 --> 00:09:29.821
Welcome to High Tide. Your Grace.

51
00:09:31.114 --> 00:09:33.324
What is the meaning of this. Lady Laena?

52
00:09:34.117 --> 00:09:36.119
Is this how House Velaryon
greets its King?

53
00:09:37.245 --> 00:09:40.039
My father has but just returned
from his long journey

54
00:09:40.790 --> 00:09:44.043
and he has hastened to the Hall of Nine
to await Your Grace's arrival.

55
00:09:47.672 --> 00:09:49.632
Let's just get on with it.

56
00:09:59.267 --> 00:10:00.727
An outsider...

57
00:10:01.728 --> 00:10:03.021
among the natives.

58
00:10:04.272 --> 00:10:05.482
Lord Larys.

59
00:10:07.233 --> 00:10:08.651
Malvales.

60
00:10:09.152 --> 00:10:10.278
A rare bloom.

61
00:10:11.780 --> 00:10:14.282
Indigenous to Braavos.

62
00:10:16.409 --> 00:10:20.079
By all rights.
it shouldn't be thriving here.

63
00:10:20.955 --> 00:10:23.708
Nature. such mystery.

64
00:10:25.043 --> 00:10:26.961
- The weather has been lovely.
- Indeed.

65
00:10:27.045 --> 00:10:28.880
And yet it is a dark day for the realm.

66
00:10:33.009 --> 00:10:34.260
Your father was a good man.

67
00:10:36.971 --> 00:10:38.473
As is yours who took his place.

68
00:10:42.435 --> 00:10:43.645
Yet still.

69
00:10:44.270 --> 00:10:46.898
the manner of your father's departure...

70
00:10:48.191 --> 00:10:50.777
it feels something of an injustice.

71
00:10:52.570 --> 00:10:54.739
What do you know of the matter
of his leaving?

72
00:10:54.823 --> 00:10:56.533
When one is never invited to speak.

73
00:10:56.616 --> 00:11:00.370
one learns instead to... observe.

74
00:11:02.664 --> 00:11:04.249
You're perhaps in need of an ally?

75
00:11:05.291 --> 00:11:06.501
I'm the Queen.

76
00:11:06.584 --> 00:11:09.003
- I have no shortage of allies.
- Naturally.

77
00:11:09.087 --> 00:11:11.089
Princess Rhaenyra. for example.

78
00:11:12.507 --> 00:11:14.133
State your purpose. my lord.

79
00:11:16.594 --> 00:11:17.804
Um...

80
00:11:17.887 --> 00:11:20.890
I did wonder if she could be relied upon

81
00:11:20.974 --> 00:11:23.601
now that she is unwell.

82
00:11:25.061 --> 00:11:28.147
Unwell? I haven't heard anything.

83
00:11:28.898 --> 00:11:30.942
Begging your pardon.
Your Grace. I may be mistaken.

84
00:11:32.610 --> 00:11:35.238
It's just that on the very same night
your father was dismissed.

85
00:11:35.321 --> 00:11:38.950
the Grand Maester delivered a tea
to the Princess's chambers.

86
00:11:41.077 --> 00:11:43.079
- A tea?
- Yes.

87
00:11:45.874 --> 00:11:48.084
That the Grand Maester himself brought?

88
00:11:48.167 --> 00:11:51.379
At the direction of the King.
as I understand it.

89
00:11:54.132 --> 00:11:56.342
I do hope she's not unwell.

90
00:11:57.844 --> 00:12:00.013
Rhaenyra sailed
with the King to Driftmark

91
00:12:00.096 --> 00:12:02.515
- yesterday at daybreak.
- Oh. what good news.

92
00:12:03.182 --> 00:12:04.392
I must've been in error.

93
00:12:05.977 --> 00:12:07.937
Ah. a relief.

94
00:12:09.814 --> 00:12:12.025
I thought for Mellos himself. well...

95
00:12:13.651 --> 00:12:15.653
her condition must be
something very serious.

96
00:12:16.905 --> 00:12:19.908
What happiness it is to have been wrong.

97
00:12:50.730 --> 00:12:51.898
I'm sorry.

98
00:12:51.981 --> 00:12:53.316
Come. cousin.

99
00:12:53.399 --> 00:12:56.027
Let us discover what might be had
for breakfast.

100
00:13:29.435 --> 00:13:30.853
Your Grace.

101
00:13:45.785 --> 00:13:47.787
Rise. Lord Corlys.

102
00:13:49.247 --> 00:13:50.540
Be welcome.

103
00:13:50.623 --> 00:13:52.250
May I offer you a chair?

104
00:13:54.085 --> 00:13:55.169
Cousin!

105
00:13:56.546 --> 00:13:57.922
Princess.

106
00:14:05.555 --> 00:14:07.765
- Are you well?
- Very.

107
00:14:08.933 --> 00:14:10.935
I congratulate you.
Lord Lyonel.

108
00:14:11.019 --> 00:14:14.230
I can think of no man more suited to be
the Hand of the King.

109
00:14:14.313 --> 00:14:17.025
That is very kind of you to say.
Lord Corlys.

110
00:14:17.108 --> 00:14:19.110
His Grace has honored me with the post.

111
00:14:21.487 --> 00:14:22.822
Pity about Ser Otto.

112
00:14:25.366 --> 00:14:28.661
Despite spending most of my days
amidst the grandeur of the Red Keep.

113
00:14:28.745 --> 00:14:31.622
the halls of High Tide
never fail to impress.

114
00:14:31.706 --> 00:14:33.374
You flatter me. Your Grace.

115
00:14:34.375 --> 00:14:37.045
Though I do wish we could meet
under happier pretenses.

116
00:14:38.588 --> 00:14:41.049
- How so?
- Daemon's wife.

117
00:14:41.132 --> 00:14:43.259
the Lady Rhea Royce. has passed.

118
00:14:44.260 --> 00:14:45.700
A hunting mishap.

119
00:14:46.679 --> 00:14:48.681
She was thrown from her horse.

120
00:14:48.765 --> 00:14:51.851
Her neck and skull
both crushed in the fall.

121
00:14:51.934 --> 00:14:54.187
A most surprising end.

122
00:14:54.270 --> 00:14:58.608
Lady Rhea's skill as both
rider and hunter were well-known.

123
00:14:58.691 --> 00:15:00.943
- The gods are cruel.
- Indeed.

124
00:15:01.819 --> 00:15:07.116
Lady Rhea was a fine woman
and a good wife to my brother.

125
00:15:07.200 --> 00:15:11.037
Sad thing that she and Daemon
have no heirs to succeed her.

126
00:15:11.120 --> 00:15:12.830
She stood to inherit Runestone.

127
00:15:13.956 --> 00:15:17.168
Mayhaps we can turn toward
happier pursuits.

128
00:15:18.002 --> 00:15:20.671
- No. thank you.
- What did you have in mind. Your Grace?

129
00:15:24.509 --> 00:15:27.845
I wish to propose a marriage
between your son. Ser Laenor...

130
00:15:28.805 --> 00:15:31.682
and my daughter and heir.
the Princess Rhaenyra.

131
00:15:31.766 --> 00:15:35.228
It's long past time our houses
were united in blood.

132
00:15:35.311 --> 00:15:37.522
The last pillars of Old Valyria.

133
00:15:38.397 --> 00:15:41.984
You honor both me
and my house. Your Grace.

134
00:15:42.068 --> 00:15:45.238
There are certain details
I would wish clarified

135
00:15:45.321 --> 00:15:48.533
before the Princess Rhaenys
and I could accept this most...

136
00:15:49.242 --> 00:15:50.868
generous proposal.

137
00:15:52.537 --> 00:15:54.163
What details?

138
00:15:56.999 --> 00:16:00.586
We would like to know
how the succession will be handled.

139
00:16:03.881 --> 00:16:06.134
Rhaenyra is my heir.

140
00:16:06.217 --> 00:16:09.428
Upon my death. my throne and my titles
will pass to her.

141
00:16:09.512 --> 00:16:12.974
She and Ser Laenor's firstborn child.
regardless of gender.

142
00:16:13.057 --> 00:16:15.685
will inherit the Iron Throne from her.

143
00:16:17.603 --> 00:16:22.733
Can I presume that.
in keeping with Westerosi tradition...

144
00:16:23.818 --> 00:16:26.445
their children would take
their father's name?

145
00:16:27.905 --> 00:16:31.284
That they would be born Velaryons?

146
00:16:31.367 --> 00:16:33.161
Surely. Lord Corlys.

147
00:16:33.244 --> 00:16:35.538
you are not proposing
the Targaryen dynasty

148
00:16:35.621 --> 00:16:38.332
end with my daughter
simply because she is a woman?

149
00:16:41.335 --> 00:16:43.963
I only seek clarity. Your Grace.

150
00:16:48.718 --> 00:16:50.303
Might I have a chair
brought in for you?

151
00:16:50.386 --> 00:16:51.387
I do not...

152
00:16:51.470 --> 00:16:53.431
No. I do not require a chair.

153
00:16:55.975 --> 00:17:00.104
Upon their birth.
Ser Laenor and Rhaenyra's children

154
00:17:00.188 --> 00:17:02.648
shall take their
father's name. Velaryon...

155
00:17:03.566 --> 00:17:06.611
in keeping with our traditions.

156
00:17:06.694 --> 00:17:08.196
However.

157
00:17:08.279 --> 00:17:12.074
at such time when their firstborn
ascends the Iron Throne.

158
00:17:12.158 --> 00:17:15.286
he or she will do so
bearing the name Targaryen.

159
00:17:16.913 --> 00:17:21.167
Dragons will rule the Seven Kingdoms
for the next hundred years.

160
00:17:21.250 --> 00:17:23.252
just as they did the last.

161
00:17:36.349 --> 00:17:38.351
This is an equitable compromise.

162
00:17:40.019 --> 00:17:41.229
Good.

163
00:17:42.104 --> 00:17:44.732
Now. if there's nothing further.

164
00:17:54.992 --> 00:17:59.330
In truth. if it had
to be someone. I'm glad it is you.

165
00:18:01.707 --> 00:18:04.335
I know this union is not
what you would choose.

166
00:18:05.586 --> 00:18:07.797
I hold nothing against you. cousin.

167
00:18:08.839 --> 00:18:10.258
No. I...

168
00:18:12.093 --> 00:18:13.302
Rather...

169
00:18:14.178 --> 00:18:16.806
Dare I say it is a matter of taste?

170
00:18:20.726 --> 00:18:23.729
I prefer roast duck to goose.

171
00:18:24.522 --> 00:18:26.148
I cannot say why.

172
00:18:29.694 --> 00:18:31.153
It's not for a lack of trying.

173
00:18:32.738 --> 00:18:34.949
There are those
who like goose very well.

174
00:18:36.701 --> 00:18:39.078
I find it a bit greasy for my taste.

175
00:18:43.416 --> 00:18:45.793
I know that whatever agreement
being struck up there

176
00:18:45.876 --> 00:18:47.837
will not change your appetites.

177
00:18:48.337 --> 00:18:50.339
nor will it change mine.

178
00:18:52.383 --> 00:18:53.426
And what do you propose?

179
00:18:59.807 --> 00:19:03.853
That we perform our duty to our fathers
and to the realm

180
00:19:03.936 --> 00:19:06.105
and when it's done...

181
00:19:06.188 --> 00:19:08.607
each of us dines as we see fit.

182
00:19:19.243 --> 00:19:22.872
Viserys has taken
to bed while his ship is readied.

183
00:19:25.333 --> 00:19:26.667
Perhaps I...

184
00:19:27.626 --> 00:19:29.045
overextended myself?

185
00:19:31.547 --> 00:19:32.965
Pushed him too close to the edge?

186
00:19:33.049 --> 00:19:35.843
My cousin chose to sail
into this tempest. husband.

187
00:19:37.720 --> 00:19:40.181
It was undignified of the King
to drag himself here

188
00:19:40.264 --> 00:19:42.600
and beg for Laenor's hand.

189
00:19:43.017 --> 00:19:44.226
Where is Laenor?

190
00:19:44.977 --> 00:19:47.438
He and Rhaenyra
are walking the coast.

191
00:19:47.521 --> 00:19:48.522
Good.

192
00:19:49.315 --> 00:19:51.942
Do they seem... familiar?

193
00:19:52.735 --> 00:19:54.335
They grew up together.

194
00:19:55.154 --> 00:19:57.698
Familiarity is not at issue.

195
00:19:57.782 --> 00:20:00.826
I'm sure Laenor
was already taken with her.

196
00:20:00.910 --> 00:20:02.828
She's grown quite comely
these last few years.

197
00:20:02.912 --> 00:20:04.705
You know his true nature.

198
00:20:06.123 --> 00:20:07.124
He's still young.

199
00:20:08.918 --> 00:20:10.086
He will outgrow it.

200
00:20:12.004 --> 00:20:14.548
There is no pleasure
in the world like...

201
00:20:16.675 --> 00:20:17.885
bedding a woman.

202
00:20:17.968 --> 00:20:20.846
We are placing our son in danger.

203
00:20:21.764 --> 00:20:24.058
The lords of the realm
bent the knee to Rhaenyra

204
00:20:24.141 --> 00:20:25.351
and swore obeisance to her.

205
00:20:25.434 --> 00:20:27.269
That was before there
was a true-born prince

206
00:20:27.353 --> 00:20:29.188
named Aegon Targaryen.

207
00:20:29.271 --> 00:20:31.440
Rhaenyra's succession
will be challenged.

208
00:20:31.941 --> 00:20:35.778
Knives will come out for her.
her husband. and for their heirs.

209
00:20:35.861 --> 00:20:39.698
Our house controls the realm's navy
and half its dragons.

210
00:20:39.782 --> 00:20:41.992
Anyone fool enough to challenge
Rhaenyra's claim

211
00:20:42.076 --> 00:20:45.329
- will be crushed.
- To what end. Corlys? Wealth? Power?

212
00:20:45.413 --> 00:20:47.039
- Pride?
- Justice.

213
00:20:52.503 --> 00:20:54.046
By all rights.

214
00:20:54.130 --> 00:20:56.173
you should be
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms.

215
00:20:58.259 --> 00:20:59.969
You were robbed
of the crown by...

216
00:21:00.052 --> 00:21:03.973
I never wore the crown
because the realm would not have it so.

217
00:21:04.056 --> 00:21:06.350
And I would remedy that

218
00:21:06.434 --> 00:21:10.020
small-minded error
by any means necessar...

219
00:21:10.104 --> 00:21:14.358
I myself have put the business
behind me. Corlys.

220
00:21:22.408 --> 00:21:25.411
I've always feared the day
you'd have to marry a woman.

221
00:21:26.412 --> 00:21:27.621
And now it comes.

222
00:21:29.039 --> 00:21:30.833
Your betrothed gives you leave

223
00:21:30.916 --> 00:21:33.335
of her own free will
to continue partaking of.

224
00:21:34.086 --> 00:21:36.338
Was I the duck or the goose?

225
00:21:36.422 --> 00:21:38.841
I've come to meet my fate
and you make a jape of it?

226
00:21:40.509 --> 00:21:42.470
Look. Rhaenyra will be
Queen of the Seven Kingdoms

227
00:21:42.553 --> 00:21:44.763
and you will be her king consort.

228
00:21:45.764 --> 00:21:47.766
Think of the tournament.

229
00:21:47.850 --> 00:21:50.102
the feast. the battles at sea.

230
00:21:53.105 --> 00:21:54.940
Will you wear your crown today.
Your Grace?

231
00:21:57.485 --> 00:21:58.903
You're a fool.

232
00:22:06.243 --> 00:22:07.703
You will need a sworn protector.

233
00:22:08.496 --> 00:22:09.497
Hmm.

234
00:22:30.226 --> 00:22:32.853
This is better
than we could've hoped for.

235
00:22:38.108 --> 00:22:40.027
She has a paramour of her own.

236
00:22:42.863 --> 00:22:44.114
<i>I wonder who it is.</i>

237
00:23:07.638 --> 00:23:10.057
Did sleep flee you as well
this morning?

238
00:23:11.350 --> 00:23:13.227
I needed to see you. Princess.

239
00:23:14.228 --> 00:23:16.230
I confess
I had a similar desire.

240
00:23:21.527 --> 00:23:26.240
You have confided in me now and then
over the years of our acquaintance.

241
00:23:26.323 --> 00:23:32.913
I feel. forgive me.
that I know you... a bit.

242
00:23:35.332 --> 00:23:36.709
You know more than a bit.

243
00:23:40.296 --> 00:23:45.509
I've heard you say so many times
how you loathe the lot of your position.

244
00:23:46.135 --> 00:23:48.512
that you are to be married off
at your father's whim

245
00:23:48.596 --> 00:23:51.181
with no thought given to the yearning
of your own heart.

246
00:23:51.265 --> 00:23:53.892
and now the day comes.

247
00:23:55.561 --> 00:23:59.481
Ser Laenor is a good and decent man.
but you did not choose him.

248
00:24:00.482 --> 00:24:03.902
- He was chosen for you.
- That's true.

249
00:24:07.281 --> 00:24:09.283
If there were another path...

250
00:24:10.367 --> 00:24:12.369
one that led to freedom...

251
00:24:13.037 --> 00:24:14.288
would you tread it?

252
00:24:16.040 --> 00:24:18.584
Rhaenyra. before I came here.

253
00:24:18.667 --> 00:24:20.878
I was a knight in the Stormlands.

254
00:24:21.629 --> 00:24:23.839
I have deep knowledge
of the port at Sunspear

255
00:24:23.922 --> 00:24:26.050
where I've seen the ships
of Essos setting sail

256
00:24:26.133 --> 00:24:28.510
with their hulls full
of oranges and cinnamon

257
00:24:28.594 --> 00:24:30.804
and I've always wished
to see where they went.

258
00:24:32.723 --> 00:24:34.350
Are you asking for leave?

259
00:24:35.726 --> 00:24:38.270
I'm asking you to come with me...

260
00:24:39.813 --> 00:24:41.815
away from all of this.

261
00:24:42.524 --> 00:24:45.486
From the burdens and indignities
of your inheritance.

262
00:24:45.569 --> 00:24:48.989
Let us leave it all behind
and see the world together...

263
00:24:50.783 --> 00:24:52.284
where we'll be nameless.

264
00:24:52.368 --> 00:24:53.994
and free...

265
00:24:54.912 --> 00:24:57.414
free to go where we like.
to love as we like.

266
00:24:59.124 --> 00:25:00.542
In Essos...

267
00:25:03.337 --> 00:25:04.963
you could marry me.

268
00:25:08.842 --> 00:25:10.594
A marriage for love.

269
00:25:10.678 --> 00:25:12.429
not for the crown.

270
00:25:37.413 --> 00:25:40.332
I am the crown. Ser Criston.

271
00:25:42.793 --> 00:25:43.919
Or I will be.

272
00:25:45.879 --> 00:25:48.465
I may chafe at my duties.

273
00:25:48.549 --> 00:25:51.719
but do you think I would choose infamy

274
00:25:51.802 --> 00:25:55.472
in exchange for a bushel of oranges
or a ship to Asshai?

275
00:25:58.892 --> 00:26:00.269
It is my duty

276
00:26:00.352 --> 00:26:03.439
to marry a nobleman from a great house

277
00:26:03.522 --> 00:26:06.066
and Ser Laenor will make a fine husband.

278
00:26:10.529 --> 00:26:12.448
But my. um...

279
00:26:13.449 --> 00:26:15.075
my marriage...

280
00:26:16.410 --> 00:26:18.579
does not have to be the end.

281
00:26:21.457 --> 00:26:26.420
Ser Criston. Laenor and I have
an understanding.

282
00:26:28.172 --> 00:26:32.092
I've granted him leave
to pursue his own interests...

283
00:26:33.135 --> 00:26:35.095
and in turn. he's granted me the same.

284
00:26:42.352 --> 00:26:44.188
So you want me to be your whore?

285
00:26:46.148 --> 00:26:49.610
I want us
to continue as we began.

286
00:26:49.693 --> 00:26:53.197
with you as my sworn protector.
my white knight.

287
00:26:53.280 --> 00:26:55.199
I took an oath.

288
00:26:56.950 --> 00:27:00.329
As a knight of your Kingsguard.

289
00:27:00.412 --> 00:27:02.372
An oath of chastity. I've broken it.

290
00:27:02.456 --> 00:27:04.958
- I won't tell anyone...
- I've soiled my white cloak.

291
00:27:05.042 --> 00:27:07.294
And it's the only thing
I have to my fucking name!

292
00:27:10.547 --> 00:27:13.967
I thought if we were married.
I might be able to restore it.

293
00:27:20.891 --> 00:27:22.935
The Iron Throne looms larger than me.

294
00:27:23.018 --> 00:27:26.605
larger than anyone in my family.

295
00:27:26.688 --> 00:27:30.317
Aegon the Conqueror
united the Seven Kingdoms

296
00:27:30.400 --> 00:27:32.402
and put them on a path...

297
00:27:33.111 --> 00:27:34.488
Ser Criston.

298
00:28:22.411 --> 00:28:23.888
- Fetch the Maester!
- Get back.

299
00:28:23.912 --> 00:28:25.664
Get Mellos! Get back!

300
00:28:25.747 --> 00:28:27.374
Prepare the crucible.

301
00:28:28.542 --> 00:28:30.377
We'll need leeches.

302
00:28:34.256 --> 00:28:35.674
Ser Criston...

303
00:28:37.092 --> 00:28:38.510
you've been summoned.

304
00:28:39.887 --> 00:28:42.097
I left the Princess just minutes ago.

305
00:28:43.015 --> 00:28:44.600
Not the Princess. ser.

306
00:28:45.267 --> 00:28:46.351
The Queen.

307
00:29:01.283 --> 00:29:02.910
Ser Criston. Your Grace.

308
00:29:07.205 --> 00:29:08.832
That will be all.

309
00:29:22.220 --> 00:29:25.724
I fear I must question you
on a delicate matter. Ser Criston.

310
00:29:28.769 --> 00:29:30.979
I am your servant as always. my Queen.

311
00:29:32.522 --> 00:29:34.733
It concerns our dear Princess Rhaenyra.

312
00:29:36.068 --> 00:29:37.277
Please.

313
00:30:03.387 --> 00:30:06.640
You are her sworn protector
and rightly loyal to her.

314
00:30:07.766 --> 00:30:09.309
I am.

315
00:30:13.146 --> 00:30:15.148
The night of Daemon's return...

316
00:30:17.901 --> 00:30:19.528
there's been a rumor...

317
00:30:20.445 --> 00:30:25.075
or rather. my father received
an accounting of...

318
00:30:26.660 --> 00:30:29.246
a lapse of morals

319
00:30:29.329 --> 00:30:33.333
that may have occurred between...

320
00:30:36.420 --> 00:30:39.589
It is. of course. unthinkable for me
to question the virtue of the Princess.

321
00:30:39.673 --> 00:30:41.633
whom I hold in highest regard.

322
00:30:41.717 --> 00:30:46.013
but. I did. however. wonder if...

323
00:30:53.353 --> 00:30:56.565
I'm not unaware
that in flush of youth...

324
00:30:57.566 --> 00:30:59.192
there may be errors made...

325
00:31:00.485 --> 00:31:03.155
breaches in resolve.

326
00:31:03.238 --> 00:31:06.241
- breaches. or rather lapses...
- It happened. Your Grace.

327
00:31:11.913 --> 00:31:13.915
The sin you allude to.

328
00:31:16.918 --> 00:31:18.253
I have committed it.

329
00:31:22.090 --> 00:31:25.093
At her instigation.
it is true. but that should...

330
00:31:26.261 --> 00:31:27.888
It is no excuse.

331
00:31:30.766 --> 00:31:32.434
My oath has been broken.

332
00:31:33.435 --> 00:31:35.062
I have dishonored myself.

333
00:31:36.730 --> 00:31:38.732
I deserve no consideration.

334
00:31:42.903 --> 00:31:44.112
But if...

335
00:31:45.238 --> 00:31:49.743
as a clement Queen.
you are inclined to pity...

336
00:31:51.119 --> 00:31:52.746
I would ask only this...

337
00:31:55.248 --> 00:31:57.834
that rather than gelding me

338
00:31:57.918 --> 00:32:00.087
and having me tortured

339
00:32:00.879 --> 00:32:03.882
you would sentence me
mercifully to death.

340
00:32:19.564 --> 00:32:21.525
Thank you for your honesty. Ser Criston.

341
00:32:32.035 --> 00:32:33.161
You may go.

342
00:33:04.317 --> 00:33:07.946
Rest now. Your Grace.
I will bring the leeches.

343
00:33:08.029 --> 00:33:10.657
Uh. if I may. Grand Maester.

344
00:33:10.740 --> 00:33:14.286
I took the liberty
of preparing a fresh set

345
00:33:14.369 --> 00:33:18.456
of herbal poultices
that might be more effective.

346
00:33:18.540 --> 00:33:21.042
That will not be necessary.
Orwyle.

347
00:33:21.126 --> 00:33:24.546
The leechings have always brought
His Grace relief.

348
00:33:43.773 --> 00:33:44.858
To help him sleep.

349
00:33:56.286 --> 00:33:57.495
Where's the Queen?

350
00:34:00.248 --> 00:34:03.335
I was given to understand that she
is otherwise occupied. Your Grace.

351
00:34:23.772 --> 00:34:25.941
Will I be remembered
as a good king. Lyonel?

352
00:34:27.984 --> 00:34:29.194
Your Grace?

353
00:34:30.278 --> 00:34:33.823
What will they say of me
when the histories are written?

354
00:34:34.741 --> 00:34:37.327
I have neither fought nor conquered.

355
00:34:37.410 --> 00:34:39.704
nor suffered any great defeat.

356
00:34:41.706 --> 00:34:44.334
Some might call that good fortune.

357
00:34:46.836 --> 00:34:49.798
It hardly makes a good song. does it?

358
00:34:49.881 --> 00:34:52.717
To be sung at feasts
in a hundred years...

359
00:34:52.801 --> 00:34:54.427
five hundred.

360
00:34:57.764 --> 00:35:00.642
You have carried
King Jaehaerys's legacy.

361
00:35:01.643 --> 00:35:04.062
And kept the realm strong.

362
00:35:04.479 --> 00:35:06.165
Is it not better
to live in peace

363
00:35:06.189 --> 00:35:09.192
than to have songs
sung after you are dead?

364
00:35:10.026 --> 00:35:11.027
Perhaps.

365
00:35:13.280 --> 00:35:16.283
But there is a part of me
wishes I'd been tested.

366
00:35:17.742 --> 00:35:20.370
I often think that in the crucible.

367
00:35:20.453 --> 00:35:23.081
I may have been forged a different man.

368
00:35:25.083 --> 00:35:29.504
Many that are tested.
only wish to have been spared it.

369
00:35:31.798 --> 00:35:34.592
Another lord might assure me
that I would rise like

370
00:35:34.676 --> 00:35:36.553
Aegon the Conqueror given the chance.

371
00:35:36.636 --> 00:35:38.676
- Your Grace. that is...
- You're right.

372
00:35:38.930 --> 00:35:41.933
You're right as always.

373
00:35:44.644 --> 00:35:47.272
It is perhaps best not to know.

374
00:36:34.986 --> 00:36:36.988
<i>It is with great pleasure</i>

375
00:36:37.072 --> 00:36:40.367
<i>that His Grace. King Viserys.
announces the start</i>

376
00:36:40.450 --> 00:36:43.078
<i>of the royal wedding celebrations.</i>

377
00:36:44.996 --> 00:36:49.292
House Lannister with their lord.
Jason Lannister.

378
00:36:49.376 --> 00:36:53.463
Lord Paramount of the West.
and Master of Casterly Rock.

379
00:36:54.672 --> 00:36:58.301
House Hightower
with their lord. Hobert Hightower.

380
00:36:58.385 --> 00:37:01.554
Beacon of the South.
Defender of the Citadel.

381
00:37:01.638 --> 00:37:02.764
the Voice of Oldtown...

382
00:37:15.777 --> 00:37:17.570
Congratulations. Your Grace.

383
00:37:17.654 --> 00:37:19.697
You have made a fine match
for the Princess.

384
00:37:19.781 --> 00:37:21.658
Thank you. Lord Jason.

385
00:37:21.741 --> 00:37:23.827
I could think of no better man
than Ser Laenor.

386
00:37:25.245 --> 00:37:27.914
Well. if this is only the welcome feast.

387
00:37:27.997 --> 00:37:31.501
I admit. I cannot imagine what you might
have planned for the wedding.

388
00:37:31.584 --> 00:37:34.003
My daughter is the future queen.

389
00:37:35.130 --> 00:37:37.924
I wanted this to be
a wedding for the histories.

390
00:37:39.467 --> 00:37:40.844
Where is the Queen?

391
00:37:40.927 --> 00:37:43.138
I had hoped to pay my respects.

392
00:37:44.681 --> 00:37:48.852
I understand the Queen is still
readying herself for the celebrations.

393
00:37:48.935 --> 00:37:51.146
This is why men wage war

394
00:37:51.938 --> 00:37:54.441
because women would never
be ready for the battle in time.

395
00:37:59.612 --> 00:38:02.240
Your presence is always
such a pleasure. Lord Jason.

396
00:38:02.323 --> 00:38:05.160
Princess. Your Grace.

397
00:38:15.336 --> 00:38:19.674
Your Grace. Princess Rhaenyra.
congratulations are in order.

398
00:38:20.425 --> 00:38:23.219
We are very honored
to have you as a guest. Ser Gerold.

399
00:38:23.303 --> 00:38:25.263
I must say. I was most distressed

400
00:38:25.346 --> 00:38:28.349
to hear of the Lady Rhea's
tragic passing.

401
00:38:29.142 --> 00:38:30.768
I'm very sorry for your loss.

402
00:38:30.852 --> 00:38:33.188
Lady Rhea
was a unique character.

403
00:38:33.813 --> 00:38:36.900
Her kind is not soon to be seen again.

404
00:38:36.983 --> 00:38:40.403
If there is anything the crown might do
to aid House Royce...

405
00:38:48.411 --> 00:38:51.372
Lord Corlys of House Velaryon.

406
00:38:51.456 --> 00:38:54.083
Lord of the Tides. Master of Driftmark.

407
00:38:54.167 --> 00:38:57.962
And his lady wife.
Princess Rhaenys Targaryen.

408
00:38:58.046 --> 00:39:01.508
And their son and heir.
Ser Laenor Velaryon.

409
00:39:01.591 --> 00:39:04.219
the future king consort.

410
00:39:45.510 --> 00:39:47.804
- My Betrothed.
- My Betrothed.

411
00:41:11.554 --> 00:41:15.558
Be welcome.
as we join together in celebration.

412
00:41:16.934 --> 00:41:18.519
Tonight is only its beginning.

413
00:41:19.395 --> 00:41:21.981
We honor the crown's oldest

414
00:41:22.065 --> 00:41:25.193
and fiercest ally. House Velaryon.

415
00:41:27.737 --> 00:41:32.408
Reaching back to the days of Old Valyria
and the Age of Dragons.

416
00:41:34.577 --> 00:41:37.580
With House Targaryen and...

417
00:42:16.411 --> 00:42:18.079
The King will not be happy.

418
00:42:18.162 --> 00:42:20.331
Right in the midst of his speech.

419
00:42:31.551 --> 00:42:33.928
The beacon on the Hightower.

420
00:42:34.011 --> 00:42:37.849
do you know what color it glows
when Oldtown calls its banners to war?

421
00:42:38.808 --> 00:42:40.017
Green.

422
00:42:51.821 --> 00:42:53.281
Congratulations. stepdaughter.

423
00:42:54.615 --> 00:42:56.033
What a blessing this is for you.

424
00:43:08.504 --> 00:43:09.839
Please be seated.

425
00:43:19.348 --> 00:43:20.433
Where was I?

426
00:43:20.516 --> 00:43:22.435
The joining of the two houses.
Your Grace.

427
00:43:22.518 --> 00:43:23.978
Yeah.

428
00:43:25.396 --> 00:43:26.814
Yes.

429
00:43:32.278 --> 00:43:37.867
With House Targaryen
and House Velaryon united.

430
00:43:37.950 --> 00:43:41.996
I hope to herald in
a second Age of Dragons

431
00:43:42.079 --> 00:43:43.498
in Westeros.

432
00:43:54.133 --> 00:43:57.136
And after
tonight's small affair...

433
00:43:59.680 --> 00:44:03.059
...seven days
of tournament and feasting.

434
00:44:06.270 --> 00:44:07.897
At the end of it all...

435
00:44:09.065 --> 00:44:12.485
At the end of it all. a royal wedding...

436
00:44:13.528 --> 00:44:14.904
between my daughter.

437
00:44:15.863 --> 00:44:17.073
my heir...

438
00:44:17.824 --> 00:44:19.033
your future Queen...

439
00:44:20.326 --> 00:44:24.163
and Ser Laenor Velaryon.
the heir to Driftmark.

440
00:45:16.924 --> 00:45:18.524
I was never much of a dancer.

441
00:45:18.593 --> 00:45:19.945
It's not much different to combat.

442
00:45:19.969 --> 00:45:22.305
Hmm.
I shall hope for a different outcome.

443
00:46:36.295 --> 00:46:39.674
- Your Grace.
- We thank you for coming. uncle.

444
00:46:39.757 --> 00:46:42.385
I worried that given leave of your
father's shadow.

445
00:46:42.468 --> 00:46:44.679
you might wither
in King's Landing's sun.

446
00:46:45.805 --> 00:46:47.807
But you stood tall.

447
00:46:49.016 --> 00:46:50.977
Know that Oldtown stands with you.

448
00:47:18.129 --> 00:47:22.174
In the Vale.
men are made to answer for their crimes.

449
00:47:24.635 --> 00:47:26.804
Even Targaryens.

450
00:47:26.887 --> 00:47:27.972
Who are you?

451
00:47:28.055 --> 00:47:31.058
Ser Gerold Royce of Runestone.

452
00:47:32.810 --> 00:47:34.186
And?

453
00:47:42.903 --> 00:47:46.490
I am cousin to your late lady wife.

454
00:47:46.574 --> 00:47:49.702
Ah. yes. Terrible thing.

455
00:47:49.785 --> 00:47:53.080
I'm positively bereft.
Such a tragic accident.

456
00:47:53.164 --> 00:47:56.125
You know better than anyone.
it was no accident.

457
00:47:56.208 --> 00:47:58.169
Are you confessing some guilt.
Ser Gerold?

458
00:47:58.252 --> 00:48:01.047
I am making an accusation.

459
00:48:03.758 --> 00:48:07.178
In King's Landing. men are made
to answer for their slanders.

460
00:48:07.261 --> 00:48:09.055
Even old bronze cunts like you.

461
00:48:11.640 --> 00:48:13.040
The truth is. I'm glad you've come.

462
00:48:13.100 --> 00:48:15.352
I wish to speak to you
about my inheritance.

463
00:48:16.520 --> 00:48:19.482
- What inheritance?
- Lady Rhea and I had no heirs.

464
00:48:19.565 --> 00:48:22.777
As her husband. whatever she was due
now passes to me.

465
00:48:24.445 --> 00:48:28.908
She stood to inherit all of Runestone.
Did she not?

466
00:48:32.411 --> 00:48:34.580
After my niece's wedding.
I plan to fly to the Eyrie

467
00:48:34.663 --> 00:48:36.207
and petition Lady Jeyne myself.

468
00:48:36.290 --> 00:48:38.292
Perhaps I'll see you there. Ser Gerold.

469
00:49:52.283 --> 00:49:55.286
Has anybody ever told you
you're nearly as pretty as your brother?

470
00:49:55.369 --> 00:49:58.164
You flatter me. my Prince.

471
00:49:58.247 --> 00:49:59.915
I was sorry to hear
about your lady wife.

472
00:49:59.999 --> 00:50:01.667
Don't be. I wasn't.

473
00:50:01.750 --> 00:50:03.502
My lady was never very kind to me.

474
00:50:03.586 --> 00:50:05.129
I know who it is.

475
00:50:05.212 --> 00:50:06.212
Hmm?

476
00:50:06.255 --> 00:50:08.215
The handsome paramour.

477
00:50:08.299 --> 00:50:09.300
Who?

478
00:50:10.217 --> 00:50:11.844
Ser Criston Cole.

479
00:50:12.595 --> 00:50:15.806
- Her sworn protector?
- Look at him.

480
00:50:15.890 --> 00:50:17.641
The man is fully cunt-struck.

481
00:50:18.767 --> 00:50:22.771
A Targaryen prince.
a dashing knight. and a dragonrider.

482
00:50:22.855 --> 00:50:24.607
You appear to be every
young maiden's dream.

483
00:50:24.690 --> 00:50:26.609
That's only because
you don't know me yet.

484
00:50:26.692 --> 00:50:29.069
I believe Ser Criston has bloodied
that white cloak of his

485
00:50:29.153 --> 00:50:31.488
- with your bride's maidenhead.
- Keep your voice down.

486
00:50:31.572 --> 00:50:33.782
Perhaps that is something
we might remedy. my Prince.

487
00:50:33.866 --> 00:50:34.867
Perhaps it is.

488
00:50:36.368 --> 00:50:38.996
This is a good thing.
She knows your secret.

489
00:50:40.206 --> 00:50:41.457
and now you know hers.

490
00:50:47.796 --> 00:50:48.881
Hey!

491
00:50:55.429 --> 00:50:56.555
Hey!

492
00:50:58.474 --> 00:50:59.683
Hey!

493
00:51:05.564 --> 00:51:06.565
Hey!

494
00:51:08.734 --> 00:51:09.818
Hey!

495
00:51:12.112 --> 00:51:14.114
They make a handsome match. don't they?

496
00:51:14.990 --> 00:51:16.283
What?

497
00:51:17.117 --> 00:51:19.119
The Princess and Ser Laenor.

498
00:51:22.498 --> 00:51:23.582
Hey!

499
00:51:28.712 --> 00:51:30.130
Ser Joffrey Lonmouth.

500
00:51:31.131 --> 00:51:32.883
or the Knight of Kisses. they call me.

501
00:51:32.967 --> 00:51:35.594
though I don't know why.

502
00:51:36.303 --> 00:51:38.031
I'm on watch.
What's your business?

503
00:51:38.055 --> 00:51:40.766
You don't know me. Ser Criston.

504
00:51:40.849 --> 00:51:43.435
But we are both deeply
invested in this union.

505
00:51:43.519 --> 00:51:44.687
Hey!

506
00:51:46.397 --> 00:51:49.566
If you have something to say.
Ser Joffrey. speak it.

507
00:51:49.650 --> 00:51:51.652
Ser Laenor is quite dear to me.

508
00:51:52.820 --> 00:51:55.990
As I know the Princess is to you.

509
00:51:57.992 --> 00:52:00.452
We should swear
to each other to guard them.

510
00:52:00.536 --> 00:52:04.123
and their secrets.
because if those are kept safe...

511
00:52:06.750 --> 00:52:07.793
then so are we all.

512
00:52:29.273 --> 00:52:30.274
Hey!

513
